text: Bainbridge is an unincorporated community in Cape Girardeau County, in the U.S. state of Missouri. ==History== A post office called Bainbridge was established in 1821, and remained in operation until 1835. The community was named after a local family who were proprietors of a ferry near the site. ==References== Category:Unincorporated communities in Cape Girardeau County, Missouri Category:Unincorporated communities in Missouri
title: Bainbridge, Missouri
